<plot>Terminal explores abandoned places, looking for their voice and beauty. Each location has imprints from those who had left years ago, forging forgotten history with its new future. The title describes not just the state of these places, but their past, as both locations were transportation hubs. Terminal explores the Buffalo Central Terminal, abandoned in the 1970's, and the subway tunnels of Rochester, the smallest city to build, and subsequently abandon, their subway.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?535840</url></doc>
